com.vmware.content

Interface TrustedCertificates

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, TrustedCertificatesTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TrustedCertificatesStub

    public interface TrustedCertificates
extends com.vmware.vapi.bindings.Service, TrustedCertificatesTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The TrustedCertificates interface provides methods to create, modify, delete and read trusted certificates. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.3.0.

    • Method Detail

      • create

        TrustedCertificates.CreateInvocation create(TrustedCertificatesTypes.CreateSpec spec)
        Adds a certificate to content library trust store.

        This API has to be invoked separately for each certificate block - (BEGIN_CERTIFICATE ... END_CERTIFICATE)

        . This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.3.0.

        Invocation Result:
        ID of the certificates added. The certificate ID will be unique for each certificate. If the certificate already exists, existing ID is returned. The return value will be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.TrustedCertificate.

        Parameters:
        spec - Specification for the certificate to be added to content library trust store.
        Returns:
        instance of TrustedCertificates.CreateInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described create operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires ContentLibrary.AddCertToTrustStore.

      • get

        TrustedCertificates.GetInvocation get(java.lang.String certificate)
        Retrieves a trusted certificate for a given certificate id. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.3.0.

        Invocation Result:
        TrustedCertificatesTypes.Info instance that corresponds to the certificate.

        Parameters:
        certificate - id of the trusted certificate. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.TrustedCertificate.
        Returns:
        instance of TrustedCertificates.GetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described get operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        NotFound - if a trusted certificate does not exist for given id.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • The resource com.vmware.content.TrustedCertificate referenced by the parameter certificate requires System.Read.

      • list

        TrustedCertificates.ListInvocation list()

        Invocation Result:

        Returns:

        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires System.Read.

      • delete

        TrustedCertificates.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String certificate)
        Deletes the trusted certificate from content library's trust store for a given identifier. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.3.0.
        Parameters:
        certificate - id of the trusted certificate. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: com.vmware.content.TrustedCertificate.
        Returns:
        instance of TrustedCertificates.DeleteInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described delete operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if the system reports an error while responding to the request.
        NotFound - if the trusted certificate specified by certificate could not be found.
        Unauthenticated - if the user can not be authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • The resource com.vmware.content.TrustedCertificate referenced by the parameter certificate requires ContentLibrary.DeleteCertFromTrustStore.
